



Sir,
Mount Vernon 9th August 1759



I am desird in a Letter which I have just received from Colo. Bassett,1 to send to you for a Chesnut horse that he has lately purchasedthe bearer awaits on you for the purpose. I was in hopes we should have had the pleasure of seeing you at Mount Vernon in yo[ur] way upMrs. Washington (who joins in her Compliments) impeaches you of a breach of promise in failure of this, and I dont know a better method of attonement, than coming soon and doubling the intended time of stay.I am Sir Yr Most Obedt Servt

Go. Washington

